        <![CDATA[This documentation describes the format of any playlist <b><code>.xml</code></b> file.
<br>
Such playlist can be saved/loaded by the Audiveris Split &amp; Merge feature or even
created/edited via any text editor.
<ul>
<li>The <b><a href="#type_playList">PlayList</a></b> class is the root of the schema.
<li>The <a href="PlayList.xsd"><b>PlayList.xsd</b></a> file contains the annotated raw schema.
</ul>
<p>
Here is an example of a playlist .xml file:
<pre>
&lt;?xml version="1.0" ?&gt;
&lt;play-list&gt;
  &lt;excerpt&gt;
    &lt;path&gt;D:\soft\audiveris-github\development\data\examples\Dichterliebe01.pdf&lt;/path&gt;
    &lt;sheets-selection&gt;2&lt;/sheets-selection&gt;
  &lt;/excerpt&gt;
  &lt;excerpt&gt;
    &lt;path&gt;D:\soft\audiveris-github\development\data\examples\chula.png&lt;/path&gt;
    &lt;sheets-selection&gt;1&lt;/sheets-selection&gt;
  &lt;/excerpt&gt;
  &lt;excerpt&gt;
    &lt;path&gt;D:\soft\audiveris-github\development\data\examples\carmen.png&lt;/path&gt;
    &lt;sheets-selection&gt;1&lt;/sheets-selection&gt;
  &lt;/excerpt&gt;
&lt;/play-list&gt;
</pre>
<p>
The diagram below presents <code>PlayList</code> and <code>Excerpt</code> 
entities and their role in the Split &amp; Merge feature:
<ol>
<li>Interactive definition or edition of a playlist
<li>Use of the playlist to build the resulting compound .omr book file.
</ol>
